        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`StartupRuntime` and `startBackgroundServicesRuntime` aggregate many unrelated callbacks (init, network, docker, logstream, transition handlers) into one injected shape.",
        "`workflowRuntime` embeds `RuntimeContainerOps`, `RuntimeUrbitOps`, and `RuntimeSnapshotOps` plus extra seams, making most workflow call sites depend on far more capabilities than each operation needs.",
        "`importerRuntime` combines storage/upload/provision/publish concerns, and most public functions accept `runtime ...importerRuntime`, so callers can pass oversized dependency sets."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split runtime bags into phase/use-case specific interfaces (for example per workflow operation, per startup phase, per importer phase) and inject only the minimal contract at each call boundary; keep a composition root that builds the full runtime once.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_callback_bag_pattern"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "importer_phase_alias_not_honest",
      "summary": "Importer phase abstractions are type aliases to one runtime, so interfaces imply separation that the type system does not enforce.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`type importerInitRuntime = importerRuntime`, `type importerWorkflowRuntime = importerRuntime`, and `type importerPublishRuntime = importerRuntime` are aliases, not constrained phase contracts.",
        "Phase-specific resolver functions (`resolveImporterRuntimeForUpload`, `resolveImporterRuntimeForPublish`, etc.) rely on runtime validation groups rather than compile-time minimal interfaces.",
        "Startup initializes importer through a single initializer path, reinforcing use of the broad runtime shape rather than explicit phase contracts."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace alias-based phase types with explicit narrow interfaces/structs per phase, then convert resolver/validator functions to construct those narrow contracts so missing phase dependencies fail at compile time.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_callback_bag_pattern"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "startup_service_registry_triplication",
      "summary": "Startup background-service abstraction is triplicated across spec list, callback map, and setter switch, increasing indirection cost and drift risk.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Service identifiers are repeated in `startBackgroundServiceSpecs`, `serviceCallbacks()`, and `setServiceCallback(...)` switch.",
        "Tests depend on helper setters (`withStartBackgroundServiceCallback`) that mirror this mapping behavior, coupling tests to mapping mechanics rather than one canonical registry.",
        "Adding a service requires synchronized edits in multiple places with no compiler guard for omissions."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define one canonical service registry (name, callback accessor, fail-fast flags, wg requirement) and generate specs plus test overrides from that single table.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_callback_bag_pattern"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "event_publish_indirection_layers",
      "summary": "Event publication uses overlapping abstraction layers (broker interface, delegating broker, and separate transition emitter seam) with minimal added policy.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/events/events.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/transitions.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`DelegatingEventBroker` forwards each method to `delegate` with only nil checks, duplicating the full `EventBroker` surface.",
        "`workflowRuntime` defines both `EventRuntime events.EventBroker` and a separate `TransitionEmitter` seam, introducing multiple publish pathways for similar concerns.",
